1.62 Mercenary TL Report <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Leveling a Mercenary at the beginning of the game can be a painful process. Due to the lack of any defensive skills until level 10 (evade), and the lack of their primary means of defense until 17 (parry) most players seem to tend to find a low-level Merc frustrating. This issue has partially been minimized due to /level, but a new player to the game doesn’t have that luxury. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>While it may be frustrating to low level mercs, this is not something we plan on looking into or changing any time in the near future.&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
Spec Line Issues: <br>
<br>
Dual Wield: <br>
<br>
Flank needs a to-hit bonus. It is one of only 2 side positionals in the game without one. Even a small one would help. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>We'll look into this during the style review.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
Dark Tendrils: Due to player feedback, I would ask that this style be reverted back to an evade reactionary. The stun in the Reflection/Hypnotic Darkness chain is too valuble. I would be interested to find out if it is possible to have a dex/qui debuff proc added to the style. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Style review again. Not necessarily sold on the dex/qui debuff proc, but be ready to make a case for it during the review.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
Crush: <br>
<br>
Bludgeon needs to have the previous style requirement, Maul, removed. This would help those who use crush to more easily keep aggro. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>See above.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
Devestate needs something added to it to make it a beneficial level 50 style. Adding a stun component, or some other effect, would make this style worthwhile. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Same.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
Parry: <br>
<br>
Parry is the primary defense of a Mercenary. It would be great to see some sort of other benefit from speccing parry, like the ability to parry arrows, or some other ability. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Really liking the idea of adding more to skills like parry and block. We're going to be looking at this going forward. Might be a TOA thing (i.e. might be something we address when we're already reworking that area of the code/design for TOA.)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
Other Issues: <br>
<br>
Determination needs to affect melee stuns as promised <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>When was this promised and by whom?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
Charge is still bugged, needs to be addressed. <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bug /appeal. Make a TL forum post detailing the bug so we can make sure it's not more of a design problem.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
Shield Spec Mercs would like Mastery of Blocking <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Reasonable request. Will see about getting that added.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Void needs to be replaced by a worthwhile RA<br>
 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>RA review should address any issues here.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <br>
Mercenaries would like to be able to purchase Avoid Pain <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Will need to look into this. Everyone wants Avoid Pain. Prepare to make a case for this during the RA review.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
Item Problems: <br>
<br>
Mercenaries would like to be able to equip Shields in the 2-handed slot, so that switching between 2 weapons and a sword and shield can be done more easily. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>We can look into this when we address other functionality/interface issues, although I am not sure how complicated this will be to address.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
